1
00:00:04,881 --> 00:00:09,291
Sometimes Gurudev and Guru Mahārāj 
would say, “Your future is so bright,

2
00:00:09,291 --> 00:00:11,801
it’s unimaginable,
you can’t conceive!”

3
00:00:11,901 --> 00:00:15,191
[Who is a Real Enjoyer— 
Devotees or Demons?]

4
00:00:15,614 --> 00:00:19,134
They’re seeing the soul,

5
00:00:19,134 --> 00:00:23,914
not a flawed covering 
of acquired prejudices;

6
00:00:23,914 --> 00:00:26,524
acquired tendencies
is karmic dress.

7
00:00:26,524 --> 00:00:29,765
They’re addressing 
the soul aspect,

8
00:00:29,765 --> 00:00:34,515
“Think, your reality potential 
is inconceivably great!

9
00:00:34,515 --> 00:00:40,625
You don’t know, 
such a bright future awaits you.”

10
00:00:43,399 --> 00:00:47,269
vṛndāraṇyaṁ sva-pada-ramaṇaṁ 
prāviśad gīta-kīrtiḥ 
[SB: 10.21.5]

11
00:00:47,269 --> 00:00:48,839
and what does it say?

12
00:00:48,839 --> 00:00:52,589
“In Vṛndāvan, 
the soil of Vṛndāvan,

13
00:00:52,589 --> 00:00:55,661
when the lotus feet of Kṛṣṇa,
as He’s walking,

14
00:00:55,661 --> 00:00:59,501
are ph-ph-ph [sound of steps]

15
00:00:59,501 --> 00:01:04,059
pressing His soft, 
inconceivably soft lotus feet,

16
00:01:04,059 --> 00:01:10,339
pressing it against 
the also soft moist soil of Vṛndāvan”.

17
00:01:10,339 --> 00:01:13,499
mridu-pade pashupangajaya

18
00:01:13,499 --> 00:01:15,519
What does it say?

19
00:01:15,524 --> 00:01:19,524
“The Earth is shivering 
in conjugal ecstasy

20
00:01:19,524 --> 00:01:24,164
at a touch 
of the lotus feet of Kṛṣṇa.”

21
00:01:26,891 --> 00:01:31,661
So who’s real hedonist, 
who’s a real sense enjoyer?

22
00:01:31,661 --> 00:01:42,511
Who wants real, never-ending, 
ever-deepening ecstasy—

23
00:01:43,164 --> 00:01:49,781
the devotee or the ... for demon 
would be another D-word.

24
00:01:49,781 --> 00:01:57,831
Devotee or demon—that has like a kind 
of assonance, alliteration going on.

25
00:01:58,565 --> 00:02:03,065
The materialist or the spiritualist? 
(Be a little more generous).

26
00:02:03,273 --> 00:02:07,273
Both are targeting pleasure,

27
00:02:07,759 --> 00:02:13,129
but one is by trying
to acquire, control,

28
00:02:13,129 --> 00:02:17,422
and consume things lower than me,
to generate that;

29
00:02:17,422 --> 00:02:22,672
the other is by offering oneself, 
one’s heart, one’s soul, oneself

30
00:02:22,672 --> 00:02:26,772
to something noble, 
worthy, higher.

31
00:02:27,527 --> 00:02:31,527
That’s why Guru Mahārāj 
appreciated those things.

32
00:02:33,488 --> 00:02:42,988
Because it reminded him of devotion, 
dedication, divinity.

